Bluestem USD 205 Bond Election
August 25 at 5:52 PM ·

Confusion about the Bluestem Bond next Tuesday? This guide will provide clarification on the two questions on the ballot and how they impact each other.

Question #1 MUST PASS for Question #2 to ELIGIBLE.

If Question #1 fails, both questions automatically fail.

Question #2 CANNOT pass on its own.

SENIOR SUNRISE
At 6:15AM on Wednesday the 26th, the seniors will be meeting at the football field to watch the sunrise and eat breakfast together. We will practice social distancing by sitting in truck beds and sitting in the grass. Make sure to bring blankets, lawn chairs, and whatever else you’ll need. We will supply donuts, orange juice, and chocolate milk. We haven’t been a class in 6 months so use this time to come together. Our senior class is a family. ONLY SENIORS WILL BE WELCOME.

post_text: Correction: BES PreK-6 Open House is scheduled for Thursday, August 20, 2020 from 5:00 pm - 7:00 pm. This will be an outside event, located on the East lawn of the elementary school. Students can drop off their school supplies and meet their teachers. Please have all supplies in a container (box, sack, or book bag) and labeled with your child's name on it. Ice cream bars and treats will be available. To help with social distancing, we ask if possible, that family names ending in A-M come from 5:00-6:00 and those ending in N-Z come from 6:00-7:00pm. There will be no BJSHS open house this year. 7th graders wishing to tour the building prior to the start of school, please contact the office. See you Thursday, go Lions!

post_text: Bluestem High School Graduation will be Sunday, May 31st at 2:00 pm in the high school parking lot. It will be a traditional ceremony. Seniors will be seated with their classmates and will go on stage to receive their diplomas. Families and guests will be able to get out of their vehicles and sit in every other parking stall. So, bring your lawn chairs and let’s celebrate our class of 2020!

post_text: Public Schools are exempt from the prohibitions in the Governor's Executive Order No 20-16 (state wide "stay home") established today under pg. 6, section 9b. The Kansas Department of Education will continue to follow Executive Order No 20-07 (temporarily closing of schools). Therefore, Mondays supply pick up and food service will continue as scheduled. Additional questions can be sent to info@usd205.com.
